parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure and oil leaks can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine makes a knocking or ticking noise
the check engine light is illuminated
and the engine fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall remedies can lead to delayed or incomplete repairs, increasing the risk of accidents or engine failure.
symptoms: The vehicle owner receives a recall notice
but the parts to repair the defect are not available
or the manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission cooling line can cause the transmission to fail, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
The failure of the brake switch can cause the vehicle's electronic stability control and downhill brake control systems to malfunction, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Electronic stability control and downhill brake control lights illuminate

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Hydraulic Brake System Failure (Service Brakes, Hydraulic)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic brake system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking power, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floorboard
ABS and Hill Descent warning lights illuminate
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recalling and repairing the hydraulic brake system can lead to a prolonged risk of accidents and injuries due to malfunctioning brakes.
symptoms: as the issue is related to the delay in recall repair rather than a specific symptom.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic brake system can cause a fire, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke coming from underneath the passenger's side of the hood

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the vehicle to catch fire, even when parked, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke coming out of the hood

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine oil leak can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds.
The lack of timely recall notification and repair can cause drivers to continue operating their vehicles with known safety defects, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Delayed or lack of recall notification
and inadequate communication from dealerships and manufacturers.
